 Nigerian government’s decision to block Twitter in the country means the country loses N90.7 million ($2250,600) every hour the microblogging platform stays shut down. This is according to estimates from the Netblocks’ Cost of Shutdown Tool (COST). A total shutdown would cost the country N2.3 billion ($5,593,819). Nigeria would also lose N48.5 billion ($134,251,654) for…